{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The National Portrait Gallery is the place dedicated"},{"time":4000,"text":"to presenting great American lives,"},{"time":6000,"text":"amazing people."},{"time":8000,"text":"And that's what it's about."},{"time":10000,"text":"We use portraiture as a way to deliver those lives, but that's it."},{"time":14000,"text":"And so I'm not going to talk about the painted portrait today."},{"time":18000,"text":"I'm going to talk about a program I started there,"},{"time":21000,"text":"which, from my point of view, is the proudest thing I did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"I started to worry about the fact"},{"time":30000,"text":"that a lot of people don't get their portraits painted anymore,"},{"time":33000,"text":"and they're amazing people,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and we want to deliver them to future generations."},{"time":38000,"text":"So, how do we do that?"},{"time":40000,"text":"And so I came up with the idea of the living self-portrait series."},{"time":42000,"text":"And the living self-portrait series was the idea of basically"},{"time":46000,"text":"my being a brush in the hand"},{"time":48000,"text":"of amazing people who would come and I would interview."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"And so what I'm going to do is, not so much give you"},{"time":54000,"text":"the great hits of that program,"},{"time":56000,"text":"as to give you this whole notion"},{"time":58000,"text":"of how you encounter people in that kind of situation,"},{"time":61000,"text":"what you try to find out about them,"},{"time":63000,"text":"and when people deliver and when they don't and why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"Now, I had two preconditions."},{"time":71000,"text":"One was that they be American."},{"time":73000,"text":"That's just because, in the nature of the National Portrait Gallery,"},{"time":76000,"text":"it's created to look at American lives."},{"time":79000,"text":"That was easy, but then I made the decision,"},{"time":82000,"text":"maybe arbitrary,"},{"time":84000,"text":"that they needed to be people of a certain age,"},{"time":88000,"text":"which at that point, when I created this program,"},{"time":90000,"text":"seemed really old."},{"time":92000,"text":"Sixties, seventies, eighties and nineties."},{"time":95000,"text":"For obvious reasons, it doesn't seem that old anymore to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"And why did I do that?"},{"time":99000,"text":"Well, for one thing, we're a youth-obsessed culture."},{"time":101000,"text":"And I thought really what we need is an elders program"},{"time":105000,"text":"to just sit at the feet of amazing people and hear them talk."},{"time":109000,"text":"But the second part of it -- and the older I get,"},{"time":113000,"text":"the more convinced I am that that's true."},{"time":116000,"text":"It's amazing what people will say when they know"},{"time":119000,"text":"how the story turned out."},{"time":121000,"text":"That's the one advantage that older people have."},{"time":125000,"text":"Well, they have other, little bit of advantage,"},{"time":127000,"text":"but they also have some disadvantages,"},{"time":129000,"text":"but the one thing they or we have is that"},{"time":131000,"text":"we've reached the point in life"},{"time":133000,"text":"where we know how the story turned out."},{"time":136000,"text":"So, we can then go back in our lives,"},{"time":138000,"text":"if we've got an interviewer who gets that,"},{"time":141000,"text":"and begin to reflect on how we got there."},{"time":145000,"text":"All of those accidents that wound up"},{"time":148000,"text":"creating the life narrative that we inherited."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"So, I thought okay, now,"},{"time":153000,"text":"what is it going to take to make this work?"},{"time":156000,"text":"There are many kinds of interviews. We know them."},{"time":158000,"text":"There are the journalist interviews,"},{"time":160000,"text":"which are the interrogation that is expected."},{"time":162000,"text":"This is somewhat against resistance"},{"time":164000,"text":"and caginess on the part of the interviewee."},{"time":168000,"text":"Then there's the celebrity interview,"},{"time":170000,"text":"where it's more important who's asking the question than who answers."},{"time":173000,"text":"That's Barbara Walters and others like that, and we like that."},{"time":177000,"text":"That's Frost-Nixon, where Frost seems to be as important"},{"time":180000,"text":"as Nixon in that process."},{"time":182000,"text":"Fair enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"But I wanted interviews that were different."},{"time":186000,"text":"I wanted to be, as I later thought of it, empathic,"},{"time":193000,"text":"which is to say, to feel what they wanted to say"},{"time":198000,"text":"and to be an agent of their self-revelation."},{"time":202000,"text":"By the way, this was always done in public."},{"time":204000,"text":"This was not an oral history program."},{"time":206000,"text":"This was all about 300 people sitting at the feet of this individual,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and having me be the brush in their self-portrait."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"Now, it turns out that I was pretty good at that."},{"time":218000,"text":"I didn't know it coming into it."},{"time":220000,"text":"And the only reason I really know that"},{"time":222000,"text":"is because of one interview I did with Senator William Fulbright,"},{"time":227000,"text":"and that was six months after he'd had a stroke."},{"time":231000,"text":"And he had never appeared in public since that point."},{"time":233000,"text":"This was not a devastating stroke,"},{"time":235000,"text":"but it did affect his speaking and so forth."},{"time":238000,"text":"And I thought it was worth a chance,"},{"time":240000,"text":"he thought it was worth a chance,"},{"time":242000,"text":"and so we got up on the stage,"},{"time":244000,"text":"and we had an hour conversation about his life,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and after that a woman rushed up to me,"},{"time":250000,"text":"essentially did,"},{"time":252000,"text":"and she said, \"Where did you train as a doctor?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"And I said, \"I have no training as a doctor. I never claimed that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"And she said, \"Well, something very weird was happening."},{"time":263000,"text":"When he started a sentence, particularly"},{"time":265000,"text":"in the early parts of the interview,"},{"time":268000,"text":"and paused, you gave him the word,"},{"time":270000,"text":"the bridge to get to the end of the sentence,"},{"time":273000,"text":"and by the end of it,"},{"time":275000,"text":"he was speaking complete sentences on his own.\""},{"time":278000,"text":"I didn't know what was going on,"},{"time":280000,"text":"but I was so part of the process of getting that out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"So I thought, okay, fine, I've got empathy,"},{"time":287000,"text":"or empathy, at any rate,"},{"time":289000,"text":"is what's critical to this kind of interview."},{"time":291000,"text":"But then I began to think of other things."},{"time":293000,"text":"Who makes a great interview in this context?"},{"time":297000,"text":"It had nothing to do with their intellect,"},{"time":299000,"text":"the quality of their intellect."},{"time":301000,"text":"Some of them were very brilliant,"},{"time":303000,"text":"some of them were,"},{"time":305000,"text":"you know, ordinary people who would never claim to be intellectuals,"},{"time":308000,"text":"but it was never about that."},{"time":311000,"text":"It was about their energy."},{"time":314000,"text":"It's energy that creates extraordinary interviews"},{"time":317000,"text":"and extraordinary lives."},{"time":319000,"text":"I'm convinced of it."},{"time":321000,"text":"And it had nothing to do with the energy of being young."},{"time":324000,"text":"These were people through their 90s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326000,"text":"In fact, the first person I interviewed"},{"time":328000,"text":"was George Abbott, who was 97,"},{"time":331000,"text":"and Abbott was filled with the life force --"},{"time":334000,"text":"I guess that's the way I think about it -- filled with it."},{"time":336000,"text":"And so he filled the room,"},{"time":338000,"text":"and we had an extraordinary conversation."},{"time":341000,"text":"He was supposed to be the toughest interview that anybody would ever do"},{"time":344000,"text":"because he was famous for being silent,"},{"time":348000,"text":"for never ever saying anything"},{"time":350000,"text":"except maybe a word or two."},{"time":352000,"text":"And, in fact, he did wind up opening up --"},{"time":354000,"text":"by the way, his energy is evidenced in other ways."},{"time":358000,"text":"He subsequently got married again at 102,"},{"time":361000,"text":"so he, you know, he had a lot of the life force in him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"But after the interview, I got a call,"},{"time":367000,"text":"very gruff voice, from a woman."},{"time":371000,"text":"I didn't know who she was,"},{"time":373000,"text":"and she said, \"Did you get George Abbott to talk?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"And I said, \"Yeah. Apparently I did.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":380000,"text":"And she said, \"I'm his old girlfriend, Maureen Stapleton,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and I could never do it.\""},{"time":386000,"text":"And then she made me go up with the tape of it"},{"time":389000,"text":"and prove that George Abbott actually could talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392000,"text":"So, you know, you want energy,"},{"time":394000,"text":"you want the life force,"},{"time":396000,"text":"but you really want them also to think"},{"time":400000,"text":"that they have a story worth sharing."},{"time":404000,"text":"The worst interviews that you can ever have"},{"time":407000,"text":"are with people who are modest."},{"time":410000,"text":"Never ever get up on a stage with somebody who's modest,"},{"time":413000,"text":"because all of these people have been assembled"},{"time":416000,"text":"to listen to them, and they sit there and they say,"},{"time":418000,"text":"\"Aw, shucks, it was an accident.\""},{"time":420000,"text":"There's nothing that ever happens that justifies"},{"time":424000,"text":"people taking good hours of the day to be with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428000,"text":"The worst interview I ever did: William L. Shirer."},{"time":431000,"text":"The journalist who did \"The Rise and Fall of the Third Reich.\""},{"time":436000,"text":"This guy had met Hitler and Gandhi within six months,"},{"time":440000,"text":"and every time I'd ask him about it, he'd say, \"Oh, I just happened to be there."},{"time":443000,"text":"Didn't matter.\" Whatever."},{"time":446000,"text":"Awful."},{"time":448000,"text":"I never would ever agree to interview a modest person."},{"time":451000,"text":"They have to think that they did something"},{"time":453000,"text":"and that they want to share it with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"But it comes down, in the end,"},{"time":459000,"text":"to how do you get through all the barriers we have."},{"time":466000,"text":"All of us are public and private beings,"},{"time":469000,"text":"and if all you're going to get from the interviewee is their public self,"},{"time":475000,"text":"there's no point in it."},{"time":477000,"text":"It's pre-programmed. It's infomercial,"},{"time":480000,"text":"and we all have infomercials about our lives."},{"time":483000,"text":"We know the great lines, we know the great moments,"},{"time":486000,"text":"we know what we're not going to share,"},{"time":488000,"text":"and the point of this was not to embarrass anybody."},{"time":491000,"text":"This wasn't -- and some of you will remember"},{"time":493000,"text":"Mike Wallace's old interviews --"},{"time":495000,"text":"tough, aggressive and so forth. They have their place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"I was trying to get them to say what they probably wanted to say,"},{"time":502000,"text":"to break out of their own cocoon of the public self,"},{"time":509000,"text":"and the more public they had been,"},{"time":511000,"text":"the more entrenched that person, that outer person was."},{"time":516000,"text":"And let me tell you at once the worse moment and the best moment"},{"time":519000,"text":"that happened in this interview series."},{"time":521000,"text":"It all has to do with that shell that most of us have,"},{"time":526000,"text":"and particularly certain people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529000,"text":"There's an extraordinary woman named Clare Boothe Luce."},{"time":532000,"text":"It'll be your generational determinant"},{"time":535000,"text":"as to whether her name means much to you."},{"time":538000,"text":"She did so much. She was a playwright."},{"time":543000,"text":"She did an extraordinary play called \"The Women.\""},{"time":546000,"text":"She was a congresswoman"},{"time":548000,"text":"when there weren't very many congresswomen."},{"time":551000,"text":"She was editor of Vanity Fair,"},{"time":553000,"text":"one of the great phenomenal women of her day."},{"time":557000,"text":"And, incidentally, I call her"},{"time":560000,"text":"the Eleanor Roosevelt of the Right."},{"time":563000,"text":"She was sort of adored on the Right"},{"time":565000,"text":"the way Eleanor Roosevelt was on the Left."},{"time":568000,"text":"And, in fact, when we did the interview --"},{"time":571000,"text":"I did the living self-portrait with her --"},{"time":573000,"text":"there were three former directors of the CIA"},{"time":575000,"text":"basically sitting at her feet,"},{"time":577000,"text":"just enjoying her presence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580000,"text":"And I thought, this is going to be a piece of cake,"},{"time":582000,"text":"because I always have preliminary talks with these people"},{"time":586000,"text":"for just maybe 10 or 15 minutes."},{"time":589000,"text":"We never talk before that because if you talk before,"},{"time":592000,"text":"you don't get it on the stage."},{"time":594000,"text":"So she and I had a delightful conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598000,"text":"We were on the stage and then --"},{"time":601000,"text":"by the way, spectacular."},{"time":603000,"text":"It was all part of Clare Boothe Luce's look."},{"time":606000,"text":"She was in a great evening gown."},{"time":609000,"text":"She was 80, almost that day of the interview,"},{"time":612000,"text":"and there she was and there I was,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and I just proceeded into the questions."},{"time":616000,"text":"And she stonewalled me. It was unbelievable."},{"time":621000,"text":"Anything that I would ask, she would turn around, dismiss,"},{"time":626000,"text":"and I was basically up there -- any of you"},{"time":628000,"text":"in the moderate-to-full entertainment world"},{"time":630000,"text":"know what it is to die onstage."},{"time":633000,"text":"And I was dying. She was absolutely not giving me a thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"And I began to wonder what was going on,"},{"time":640000,"text":"and you think while you talk,"},{"time":642000,"text":"and basically, I thought, I got it."},{"time":645000,"text":"When we were alone, I was her audience."},{"time":649000,"text":"Now I'm her competitor for the audience."},{"time":651000,"text":"That's the problem here, and she's fighting me for that,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and so then I asked her a question --"},{"time":657000,"text":"I didn't know how I was going to get out of it --"},{"time":659000,"text":"I asked her a question about her days as a playwright,"},{"time":665000,"text":"and again, characteristically,"},{"time":667000,"text":"instead of saying, \"Oh yes, I was a playwright, and this is what blah blah blah,\""},{"time":670000,"text":"she said, \"Oh, playwright. Everybody knows I was a playwright."},{"time":673000,"text":"Most people think that I was an actress. I was never an actress.\""},{"time":677000,"text":"But I hadn't asked that, and then she went off on a tear,"},{"time":681000,"text":"and she said, \"Oh, well, there was that one time that I was an actress."},{"time":684000,"text":"It was for a charity in Connecticut when I was a congresswoman,"},{"time":687000,"text":"and I got up there,\" and she went on and on, \"And then I got on the stage.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":690000,"text":"And then she turned to me and said,"},{"time":692000,"text":"\"And you know what those young actors did?"},{"time":695000,"text":"They upstaged me.\" And she said, \"Do you know what that is?\""},{"time":697000,"text":"Just withering in her contempt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699000,"text":"And I said, \"I'm learning.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":701000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":703000,"text":"And she looked at me, and it was like the successful arm-wrestle,"},{"time":708000,"text":"and then, after that, she delivered an extraordinary account"},{"time":712000,"text":"of what her life really was like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714000,"text":"I have to end that one. This is my tribute to Clare Boothe Luce."},{"time":717000,"text":"Again, a remarkable person."},{"time":719000,"text":"I'm not politically attracted to her, but through her life force,"},{"time":722000,"text":"I'm attracted to her."},{"time":725000,"text":"And the way she died -- she had, toward the end, a brain tumor."},{"time":730000,"text":"That's probably as terrible a way to die as you can imagine,"},{"time":733000,"text":"and very few of us were invited to a dinner party."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739000,"text":"And she was in horrible pain."},{"time":741000,"text":"We all knew that."},{"time":743000,"text":"She stayed in her room."},{"time":746000,"text":"Everybody came. The butler passed around canapes."},{"time":748000,"text":"The usual sort of thing."},{"time":751000,"text":"Then at a certain moment, the door opened"},{"time":754000,"text":"and she walked out perfectly dressed, completely composed."},{"time":758000,"text":"The public self, the beauty, the intellect,"},{"time":762000,"text":"and she walked around and talked to every person there"},{"time":766000,"text":"and then went back into the room and was never seen again."},{"time":769000,"text":"She wanted the control of her final moment, and she did it amazingly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"Now, there are other ways that you get somebody to open up,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and this is just a brief reference."},{"time":783000,"text":"It wasn't this arm-wrestle,"},{"time":785000,"text":"but it was a little surprising for the person involved."},{"time":787000,"text":"I interviewed Steve Martin. It wasn't all that long ago."},{"time":791000,"text":"And we were sitting there,"},{"time":793000,"text":"and almost toward the beginning of the interview,"},{"time":796000,"text":"I turned to him and I said, \"Steve,\" or \"Mr. Martin,"},{"time":801000,"text":"it is said that all comedians have unhappy childhoods."},{"time":807000,"text":"Was yours unhappy?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":809000,"text":"And he looked at me, you know, as if to say,"},{"time":812000,"text":"\"This is how you're going to start this thing, right off?\""},{"time":815000,"text":"And then he turned to me, not stupidly,"},{"time":817000,"text":"and he said, \"What was your childhood like?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":821000,"text":"And I said -- these are all arm wrestles, but they're affectionate --"},{"time":824000,"text":"and I said, \"My father was loving and supportive,"},{"time":827000,"text":"which is why I'm not funny.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":829000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"And he looked at me, and then we heard the big sad story."},{"time":835000,"text":"His father was an SOB,"},{"time":837000,"text":"and, in fact, he was another comedian with an unhappy childhood,"},{"time":841000,"text":"but then we were off and running."},{"time":844000,"text":"So the question is:"},{"time":845000,"text":"What is the key that's going to allow this to proceed?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":848000,"text":"Now, these are arm wrestle questions,"},{"time":850000,"text":"but I want to tell you about questions"},{"time":853000,"text":"that are more related to empathy"},{"time":856000,"text":"and that really, very often, are the questions"},{"time":859000,"text":"that people have been waiting their whole lives to be asked."},{"time":862000,"text":"And I'll just give you two examples of this because of the time constraints."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866000,"text":"One was an interview I did with one of the great American biographers."},{"time":872000,"text":"Again, some of you will know him, most of you won't, Dumas Malone."},{"time":874000,"text":"He did a five-volume biography of Thomas Jefferson,"},{"time":878000,"text":"spent virtually his whole life with Thomas Jefferson,"},{"time":883000,"text":"and by the way, at one point I asked him,"},{"time":885000,"text":"\"Would you like to have met him?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"And he said, \"Well, of course,"},{"time":889000,"text":"but actually, I know him better than anyone who ever met him,"},{"time":892000,"text":"because I got to read all of his letters.\""},{"time":894000,"text":"So, he was very satisfied with the kind of relationship they had over 50 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900000,"text":"And I asked him one question."},{"time":903000,"text":"I said, \"Did Jefferson ever disappoint you?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":907000,"text":"And here is this man who had given his whole life to uncovering Jefferson"},{"time":912000,"text":"and connecting with him,"},{"time":914000,"text":"and he said, \"Well ...\" -- I'm going to do a bad southern accent."},{"time":919000,"text":"Dumas Malone was from Mississippi originally."},{"time":922000,"text":"But he said, \"Well,\" he said, \"I'm afraid so.\""},{"time":926000,"text":"He said, \"You know, I've read everything,"},{"time":929000,"text":"and sometimes Mr. Jefferson would smooth the truth a bit.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":937000,"text":"And he basically was saying that this was a man"},{"time":940000,"text":"who lied more than he wished he had,"},{"time":943000,"text":"because he saw the letters."},{"time":945000,"text":"He said, \"But I understand that.\" He said, \"I understand that.\""},{"time":949000,"text":"He said, \"We southerners do like a smooth surface,"},{"time":954000,"text":"so that there were times when he just didn't want the confrontation.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":958000,"text":"And he said, \"Now, John Adams was too honest.\""},{"time":962000,"text":"And he started to talk about that, and later on he invited me to his house,"},{"time":965000,"text":"and I met his wife who was from Massachusetts,"},{"time":967000,"text":"and he and she had exactly the relationship"},{"time":970000,"text":"of Thomas Jefferson and John Adams."},{"time":973000,"text":"She was the New Englander and abrasive,"},{"time":975000,"text":"and he was this courtly fellow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978000,"text":"But really the most important question I ever asked,"},{"time":981000,"text":"and most of the times when I talk about it,"},{"time":984000,"text":"people kind of suck in their breath at my audacity, or cruelty,"},{"time":989000,"text":"but I promise you it was the right question."},{"time":993000,"text":"This was to Agnes de Mille."},{"time":996000,"text":"Agnes de Mille is one of the great choreographers in our history."},{"time":1000000,"text":"She basically created the dances in \"Oklahoma,\""},{"time":1004000,"text":"transforming the American theater."},{"time":1006000,"text":"An amazing woman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008000,"text":"At the time that I proposed to her that --"},{"time":1013000,"text":"by the way, I would have proposed to her; she was extraordinary --"},{"time":1015000,"text":"but proposed to her that she come on."},{"time":1017000,"text":"She said, \"Come to my apartment.\""},{"time":1019000,"text":"She lived in New York."},{"time":1021000,"text":"\"Come to my apartment and we'll talk for those 15 minutes,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"and then we'll decide whether we proceed.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027000,"text":"And so I showed up in this dark, rambling New York apartment,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"and she called out to me, and she was in bed."},{"time":1035000,"text":"I had known that she had had a stroke,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"and that was some 10 years before."},{"time":1039000,"text":"And so she spent almost all of her life in bed,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"but -- I speak of the life force --"},{"time":1046000,"text":"her hair was askew."},{"time":1048000,"text":"She wasn't about to make up for this occasion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051000,"text":"And she was sitting there surrounded by books,"},{"time":1054000,"text":"and her most interesting possession she felt at that moment"},{"time":1058000,"text":"was her will, which she had by her side."},{"time":1064000,"text":"She wasn't unhappy about this. She was resigned."},{"time":1068000,"text":"She said, \"I keep this will by my bed, memento mori,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"and I change it all the time"},{"time":1077000,"text":"just because I want to.\""},{"time":1079000,"text":"And she was loving the prospect of death as much as she had loved life."},{"time":1084000,"text":"I thought, this is somebody I've got to get in this series."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087000,"text":"She agreed."},{"time":1089000,"text":"She came on. Of course she was wheelchaired on."},{"time":1092000,"text":"Half of her body was stricken, the other half not."},{"time":1095000,"text":"She was, of course, done up for the occasion,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"but this was a woman in great physical distress."},{"time":1102000,"text":"And we had a conversation,"},{"time":1105000,"text":"and then I asked her this unthinkable question."},{"time":1108000,"text":"I said, \"Was it a problem for you in your life that you were not beautiful?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1117000,"text":"And the audience just -- you know,"},{"time":1120000,"text":"they're always on the side of the interviewee,"},{"time":1123000,"text":"and they felt that this was a kind of assault,"},{"time":1126000,"text":"but this was the question she had"},{"time":1128000,"text":"wanted somebody to ask her whole life."},{"time":1131000,"text":"And she began to talk about her childhood, when she was beautiful,"},{"time":1136000,"text":"and she literally turned -- here she was, in this broken body --"},{"time":1139000,"text":"and she turned to the audience and"},{"time":1142000,"text":"described herself as the fair demoiselle"},{"time":1144000,"text":"with her red hair and her light steps and so forth,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"and then she said, \"And then puberty hit.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1153000,"text":"And she began to talk about things that had happened"},{"time":1155000,"text":"to her body and her face,"},{"time":1157000,"text":"and how she could no longer count on her beauty,"},{"time":1161000,"text":"and her family then treated her like the ugly sister of the beautiful one"},{"time":1168000,"text":"for whom all the ballet lessons were given."},{"time":1170000,"text":"And she had to go along just to be with her sister for company,"},{"time":1175000,"text":"and in that process, she made a number of decisions."},{"time":1178000,"text":"First of all, was that dance, even though"},{"time":1180000,"text":"it hadn't been offered to her, was her life."},{"time":1182000,"text":"And secondly, she had better be,"},{"time":1184000,"text":"although she did dance for a while, a choreographer"},{"time":1186000,"text":"because then her looks didn't matter."},{"time":1189000,"text":"But she was thrilled to get that out as a real, real fact in her life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1196000,"text":"It was an amazing privilege to do this series."},{"time":1201000,"text":"There were other moments like that, very few moments of silence."},{"time":1207000,"text":"The key point was empathy"},{"time":1210000,"text":"because everybody in their lives"},{"time":1214000,"text":"is really waiting for people to ask them questions,"},{"time":1218000,"text":"so that they can be truthful about who they are"},{"time":1220000,"text":"and how they became what they are,"},{"time":1223000,"text":"and I commend that to you, even if you're not doing interviews."},{"time":1227000,"text":"Just be that way with your friends"},{"time":1229000,"text":"and particularly the older members of your family."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1232000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}